name: Prague Castle
opening_hours_note: Complex generally 06:00–22:00; interiors and specific sites have varied hours.
ticket_info_note: Courtyards free; paid circuits for interiors and exhibitions.
short_description_en: Largest ancient castle complex in the world, seat of Czech rulers and presidents with cathedrals, palaces and panoramic city views.

name: St. Vitus Cathedral
opening_hours_note: Opening hours vary seasonally within Prague Castle opening times.
ticket_info_note: Partly accessible with Prague Castle ticket circuits.
short_description_en: Gothic cathedral dominating the castle skyline, housing royal tombs and stunning stained glass windows.

name: Charles Bridge
ticket_info_note: Free to cross; paid entry to bridge towers.
short_description_en: Historic stone bridge lined with Baroque statues, offering iconic views of the Vltava River and Prague Castle.

name: Old Town Square
opening_hours_note: Public square open 24/7; individual buildings have own hours.
ticket_info_note: Square is free; tower and interiors ticketed.
short_description_en: Central historic square surrounded by churches, colorful facades and the famous Astronomical Clock.

name: Prague Astronomical Clock
opening_hours_note: Tower visiting hours vary by season; hourly show during daytime.
ticket_info_note: Paid entry to the Old Town Hall tower; exterior show is free.
short_description_en: Medieval astronomical clock with animated hourly show and panoramic city views from the tower.

name: Jewish Quarter (Josefov)
opening_hours_note: Synagogues and cemetery have set hours; often closed on Saturdays and Jewish holidays.
ticket_info_note: Combined tickets for synagogues and Old Jewish Cemetery.
short_description_en: Historic Jewish district with synagogues, cemetery and museums telling the story of Prague's Jewish community.

name: Petrin Hill & Lookout Tower
opening_hours_note: Park open 24/7; tower and funicular have specific hours.
ticket_info_note: Ticketed entry for the lookout tower and funicular.
short_description_en: Large hillside park with gardens, mirror maze and an Eiffel-style lookout tower overlooking Prague.

name: Wenceslas Square
opening_hours_note: Public space open 24/7; shops and museums have individual hours.
ticket_info_note: No ticket for the square itself.
short_description_en: Long historic boulevard that has hosted key Czech demonstrations, now lined with shops, hotels and the National Museum.

name: National Museum
opening_hours_note: Typically open daily except selected holidays, often 10:00–18:00.
ticket_info_note: Paid entry; combined tickets sometimes available for exhibitions.
short_description_en: Flagship Czech museum with grand interiors and exhibitions on natural history and national heritage.

name: Dancing House
opening_hours_note: Rooftop bar and gallery have set opening hours.
ticket_info_note: Free to view from outside; rooftop and exhibitions ticketed.
short_description_en: Iconic modern riverside building nicknamed 'Fred and Ginger' with a rooftop terrace overlooking the Vltava.

name: Municipal House
opening_hours_note: Guided tours and cafes have defined hours; evening concerts common.
ticket_info_note: Paid tours and concert tickets; cafes open to the public.
short_description_en: Lavish Art Nouveau cultural venue with richly decorated interiors, cafes and a major concert hall.

name: House of the Black Madonna
opening_hours_note: Museum and cafe have standard daytime hours.
ticket_info_note: Museum ticket required for exhibitions; cafe free entry.
short_description_en: Pioneering Cubist building housing a design museum and a historic Grand Cafe.

name: Vysehrad Fortress
opening_hours_note: Park area open; interiors and cemetery have separate hours.
ticket_info_note: Most outdoor areas free; some sites ticketed.
short_description_en: Historic hilltop fortress with peaceful park, river views, cemetery and legends older than Prague Castle.

name: Letna Park
ticket_info_note: No ticket required; pay at beer gardens.
short_description_en: Large park with beer gardens and some of the best panoramic views over Prague's bridges.

name: National Theatre
opening_hours_note: Evening performances; guided tours on selected days.
ticket_info_note: Tickets required for performances and some tours.
short_description_en: Golden-roofed national stage for opera, ballet and drama with richly decorated interiors.
